---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="🥒 Pickles — Elena Tănăsoiu" description="An authoritative ranking of pickles.">
  <Nav />

  <main class="flex-1 pt-28 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-2">🥒 The Definitive Pickle Ranking</h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mb-8">
        You found the secret page. As a performance engineer who
        <em>"enjoys pickles and flamegraphs"</em>, I feel it's my duty to rank them.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">🥇</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Cornichons</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">The tiny, crunchy, French ones. Peak pickle performance. O(1) crunch time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">🥈</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Half-sour Dill</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Still has some crunch left. Like code that's been partially optimised — room to grow.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">🥉</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Bread & Butter</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Sweet and tangy. The comfort food of pickles. Reliable like a well-tested codebase.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl">4.</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Classic Dill</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">The default. Like Ruby on Rails — gets the job done, everyone has an opinion.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl">5.</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Pickled Onions</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Not technically a pickle but I'll allow it. Like Go in a Ruby shop — unexpected but effective.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-surface-800 border border-surface-600 rounded-xl p-6 opacity-60">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
            <span class="text-2xl">∞</span>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-text-primary font-semibold text-lg">Sweet Gherkins</h2>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Too sweet. Like over-engineering. Sometimes less is more.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-text-muted text-xs mt-12 text-center font-mono">
        This ranking is final and not up for debate. Any PRs will be closed without comment.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="text-flame-400 hover:text-flame-300 text-sm font-medium">
          ← Back to serious engineering content
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
